Measuring Impact
 
 






Measuring Impact
A key component of impact investing is tracking, analyzing and reporting the impact of investments. TriLinc supports the Impact Reporting and Investment Standards (IRIS) metrics taxonomy for measuring the economic, social and environmental impact of individual investments. IRIS is the catalog of generally-accepted performance metrics that leading impact investors use to measure social, environmental and financial success. By providing a standard common language to describe social and environmental performance, IRIS makes it easier to compare investments and ensure consistent measurement across various investment opportunities.



TRACK
ANALYZE
REPORT




Identify Measurable & Meaningful Impact Metrics 
Incorporate Metrics into Portfolio Management Platform
Produce Quarterly & Annual Reports




Metrics selected to track progress towards investment-specific economic, environmental and social impact objectives




Impact metrics reviewed alongside financial metrics to assess both aspects of an investment’s performance




Quantitative impact results reported through portfolio management platform


Qualitative borrower impact stories




Create Easily Reportable Data Collection Screens & Forms
Aggregate Data to Measure Progress Against Core Impact Objectives
Contribute to Standardization of Impact Measurement




Screens employed during investment due diligence




Impact dashboards customized to analyze data by industry, sector and individual investment




IRIS metrics reported through various impact industry channels






Initial and annual data collection incorporated into sub-advisor underwriting process





Collaboration with industry leaders on refining best practices


















 


